title: Batman
description: The Dark Knight of Gotham City begins his war on crime with his first major enemy being Jack Napier, a criminal who becomes the clownishly homicidal Joker.

title: Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade
description: In 1938, after his father Professor Henry Jones, Sr. goes missing while pursuing the Holy Grail, Indiana Jones finds himself up against Adolf Hitler's Nazis again to stop them from obtaining its powers.

title: Dead Poets Society
oscars_won_details: Best Writing, Screenplay Written Directly for the Screen
description: Maverick teacher John Keating returns to his strict all-boys preparatory school and makes use of unconventional methods to reach out to his students, who face enormous pressures from their parents and the school.

title: Do the Right Thing
description: On the hottest day of the year on a street in the Bedford-Stuyvesant section of Brooklyn, everyone's hate and bigotry smolders and builds until it explodes into violence.

title: Driving Miss Daisy
oscars_won_details: Best Actress in a Leading Role
Best Writing, Screenplay Based on Material from Another Medium
description: An old Jewish woman and her African-American chauffeur in the American South have a relationship that grows and improves over the years.

title: Glory
oscars_won_details: Best Actor in a Supporting Role
description: Robert Gould Shaw leads the U.S. Civil War's first all-black volunteer company, fighting prejudices from both his own Union Army, and the Confederates.

title: The Little Mermaid
description: A mermaid princess makes a Faustian bargain in an attempt to become human and win a prince's love.

title: Born on the Fourth of July
description: The biography of Ron Kovic. Paralyzed in the Vietnam war, he becomes an anti-war and pro-human rights political activist after feeling betrayed by the country he fought for.

title: Field of Dreams
description: Iowa farmer Ray Kinsella is inspired by a voice he can't ignore to pursue a dream he can hardly believe. Supported by his wife, Ray begins the quest by turning his ordinary cornfield into a place where dreams can come true.

title: When Harry Met Sally...
description: Harry and Sally have known each other for years, and are very good friends, but they fear sex would ruin the friendship.

title: Sex, Lies, and Videotape
description: A sexually repressed woman's husband is having an affair with her sister. The arrival of a visitor with a rather unusual fetish changes everything.

title: My Left Foot
oscars_won_details: Best Actor in a Leading Role
Best Actress in a Supporting Role
description: Christy Brown, born with cerebral palsy, learns to paint and write with his only controllable limb - his left foot.

title: Crimes and Misdemeanors
description: An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife, while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated by another woman.

title: Say Anything...
description: A noble underachiever and a beautiful valedictorian fall in love the summer before she goes off to college.

title: The Abyss
description: A civilian diving team is enlisted to search for a lost nuclear submarine and encounters an alien aquatic species.

title: Steel Magnolias
description: A young beautician, newly arrived in a small Louisiana town, finds work at the local salon, where a small group of women share a close bond of friendship, and welcome her into the fold.

title: Back to the Future Part II
description: After visiting 2015, Marty McFly must repeat his visit to 1955 to prevent disastrous changes to 1985...without interfering with his first trip.

title: Lethal Weapon 2
description: Riggs and Murtaugh are on the trail of South African diplomats who are using their immunity to engage in criminal activities.

title: Honey, I Shrunk the Kids
description: The scientist father of a teenage girl and boy accidentally shrinks his and two other neighborhood teens to the size of insects. Now the teens must fight diminutive dangers as the father searches for them.

title: Parenthood
description: The Buckman family struggles to raise their children in the right way.

title: The War of the Roses
description: A married couple tries everything to get each other to leave the house in a vicious divorce battle.

title: National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation
description: The Griswold family's plans for a big family Christmas predictably turn into a big disaster.

title: Uncle Buck
description: Bachelor and all-round slob Buck Russell babysits his brother's rebellious teenage daughter and her cute younger brother and sister.

title: Major League
description: The new owner of the Cleveland Indians puts together a purposely horrible team so they'll lose and she can move the team. But when the plot is uncovered, they start winning just to spite her.

title: Sea of Love
description: A detective investigating a series of murders becomes involved with a woman who may be the culprit.

title: The Fabulous Baker Boys
description: The lives of two struggling jazz musicians are turned upside down when they hire a beautiful singer.

title: Licence to Kill
description: James Bond goes rogue and sets off to unleash vengeance on a drug lord who tortured his best friend, a C.I.A. agent, and left him for dead and murdered his bride after he helped capture him.

title: Black Rain
description: Two New York City cops get involved in a gang war between members of the Yakuza, the Japanese Mafia.

title: Ghostbusters II
description: The discovery of a massive river of ectoplasm and a resurgence of spectral activity allows the Ghostbusters to revive the business.

title: Pet Sematary
description: After tragedy strikes, a grieving father discovers an ancient burial ground behind his home with the power to raise the dead.

title: Road House
description: A tough bouncer is hired to tame a dirty bar.

title: Bill & Ted's Excellent Adventure
description: Two rock-'n-rolling teens travel through time to secure their place in history.

title: Heathers
description: In order to get out of the snobby clique that is destroying her good-girl reputation, an intelligent teen teams up with a dark sociopath in a plot to kill the cool kids.

title: Drugstore Cowboy
description: A pharmacy-robbing dope fiend and his crew pop pills and evade the law.

title: Roger & Me
description: Director Michael Moore pursues GM CEO Roger Smith to confront him about the harm he did to Flint, Michigan with his massive downsizing.

title: Henry V
description: In the midst of the Hundred Years' War, the young King Henry V of England embarks on the conquest of France in 1415.

title: The Cook, the Thief, His Wife & Her Lover
description: The wife of a barbaric crime boss engages in a secretive romance with a gentle bookseller between meals at her husband's restaurant.

title: Kiki's Delivery Service
description: A young witch, on her mandatory year of independent life, finds fitting into a new community difficult while she supports herself by running an air courier service.

title: The Killer
description: A disillusioned assassin accepts one last hit in hopes of using his earnings to restore vision to a singer he accidentally blinded.

title: Mystery Train
description: Three stories concerning different groups of people intertwine in a Memphis hotel, dedicated to Elvis Presley.

title: Santa Sangre
description: A former circus artist escapes from a mental hospital to rejoin his armless mother - the leader of a strange religious cult - and is forced to enact brutal murders in her name.

title: Tetsuo: The Iron Man
description: A "metal fetishist", driven mad by the maggots wriggling in the wound he's made to embed metal into his leg, runs out into the night and is accidentally run down by a Japanese businessman and his girlfriend.

title: Jesus of Montreal
description: A group of actors put on an unorthodox passion play which incites the opposition of the Catholic Church while the actors' lives begin to mirror the Passion itself.

title: A Dry White Season
description: A white South African schoolteacher's quiet life is turned upside down when he discovers the brutality of the apartheid system.

title: Enemies, A Love Story
description: A Holocaust survivor finds himself involved with three women in 1949 New York.

title: Music Box
description: A lawyer defends her father accused of war crimes, but there is more to the case than she suspects.

title: Casualties of War
description: During the Vietnam War, a soldier finds himself the outsider of his own squad when they unnecessarily kidnap a female villager.

title: The Bear
description: An orphan bear cub hooks up with an adult male as they try to dodge human hunters.

title: Shirley Valentine
description: Shirley Valentine is a bored 42-year-old housewife who takes a holiday in Greece and meets a tavern owner who helps her rediscover the woman she used to be.

title: Lean on Me
description: The dedicated but tyrannical Joe Clark is appointed the principal of a decaying inner-city school and he is determined to improve by any means necessary.

title: The 'Burbs
description: An overstressed suburbanite and his neighbors are convinced that the new family on the block are part of a murderous Satanic cult.

title: UHF
description: A daydreamer becomes the manager of a small television station and creates a series of bizarre and popular shows.

title: The Dream Team
description: Four mental patients are separated from their therapist during a field trip to New York City and must try to find him and navigate the big city on their own.
